Claims CLAIMS  What is claimed: 1. A method performed by a wireless transmit / receive unit (WTRU), the method comprising: receiving a common feedback transmission, in response to a transmission of the WTRU, wherein the common feedback transmission conveys one or both of a preamble and a demodulation reference signal (DMRS) to indicate an identifier of the WTRU; determining whether a preamble-to-DMRS association is configured; on a condition the preamble-to-DMRS association is not configured, determining to use both the preamble and the DMRS as the identifier of the WTRU; and on a condition the preamble-to-DMRS association is configured, determining to use one of the preamble or the DMRS as the identifier of the WTRU based on the preamble-to-DMRS association. 2. The method of claim 1 , wherein the transmission of the WTRU is a data transmission. 3. The method of claim 1 , wherein the transmission of the WTRU is a random access transmission. 4. The method of claim 1 , wherein the common feedback transmission is a non- orthogonal multiple access (NOMA) type transmission. 5. The method of claim 1 , further comprising: receiving an indication of the preamble-to-DMRS association. 6. The method of claim 1 , wherein the preamble-to-DMRS association is based on a resource pool configuration. 7. The method of claim 1 , wherein the preamble-to-DMRS association is a one-to-one, one-to-many or many-to-one type association. 8. The method of claim 1 , wherein the preamble is determined as the identifier of the WTRU. 9. The method of claim 1 , wherein the DMRS is determined as the identifier of the WTRU. 10. The method of claim 1 , wherein a radio network temporary identifier (RNTI) is used as the identifier of the WTRU in combination with one or both of the preamble and the DMRS. 1 1. The method of claim 1 , further comprising: 

 determining, based on the identifier of the WTRU and the common feedback transmission, that the transmission of the WTRU has been successfully received by a next generation Node B (gNB). 12. A method performed by a wireless transmit / receive unit (WTRU), the method comprising: receiving a common feedback transmission, in response to a transmission of the WTRU, wherein the common feedback transmission conveys one or both of a preamble and a demodulation reference signal (DMRS) to indicate an identifier of the WTRU; determining whether a preamble-to-DMRS association is configured; on a condition the preamble-to-DMRS association is not configured, determining to use both the preamble and the DMRS as the identifier of the WTRU; on a condition the preamble-to-DMRS association is configured, determining to use one of the preamble or the DMRS as the identifier of the WTRU based on the preamble-to-DMRS association; and determining to use another identifier, in combination with one or both of the preamble and the DMRS, as the identifier of the WTRU. 13. The method of claim 12, wherein the another identifier is a radio network temporary identifier (RNTI). 14. The method of claim 13, wherein the RNTI is a cell-RNTI (C-RNTI). 15. The method of claim 13, wherein the another identifier is an NM-RNTI. 16. The method of claim 13, wherein the another identifier is a group common physical downlink control channel (GC-PDCCH) identifier. 17. The method of claim 13, wherein the another identifier is a multiple access signature. 18. The method of claim 12, wherein the another identifier is an IMSI or the another identifier is a random number generated by the WTRU. 19. The method of claim 12, further comprising: determining, based on the identifier of the WTRU and the common feedback transmission, that the transmission of the WTRU has been successfully received by a next generation Node B (gNB). 20. A wireless transmit / receive unit (WTRU) comprising: a receiver configured to receive a common feedback transmission, in response to a transmission of the WTRU, wherein the common feedback transmission conveys one or both of a preamble and a demodulation reference signal (DMRS) to indicate an identifier of the WTRU; 

 circuitry configured to determine whether a preamble-to-DMRS association is configured; circuitry configured to, on a condition the preamble-to-DMRS association is not configured, determine to use both the preamble and the DMRS as the identifier of the WTRU; circuitry configured to, on a condition the preamble-to-DMRS association is configured, determine to use one of the preamble or the DMRS as the identifier of the WTRU, based on the preamble-to-DMRS association; and circuitry configured to determine to use another identifier, in combination with one or both of the preamble and the DMRS, as the identifier of the WTRU.
